ENTRY            A0554   20260203   20260327   20260327       A130
SUBENT        A0554001   20260203   20260327   20260327       A130
BIB                  8         24
TITLE      No evidence of break-up effects on the fusion of 9-Be
           with medium-light nuclei.
AUTHOR     (R.M.Anjos,C.Muri,J.Lubian,P.R.S.Gomes,I.Padron,
           J.J.S.Alves,G.V.Marti,J.O.Fernandes Niello,
           A.J.Pacheco,O.A.Capurro,D.Abriola,J.E.Testoni,
           M.Ramirez,R.Liguori Neto,N.Added)
REFERENCE  (J,PL/B,534,45,2002)
           (J,PR/C,70,054605,2004) Elastic scattering data
REL-REF    (N,,A.Gavron,J,PR/C,21,230,1980)
           Statistical code PACE.
INSTITUTE  (3BZLUFF,3ARGCNE,3BZLUSP)
METHOD     (EDE) The resolution in both experiments was good
           enough to separate events differing by one unity of
           atomic number.
           (SITA)
PART-DET   (RSD)
HISTORY    (20030802C)
           (20030815R) Data tables were received from J.Lubian
           (20030820R) Data table for elastic scattering was
           received from J.Lubian
           (20051026A) Additional reference is added. FACILITY is
           added to SUBENT A0554005
           (20051026U) Last checking has been done.
           (20260203U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              24
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           27
SUBENT        A0554002   20260203   20260327   20260327       A130
BIB                 10         25
REACTION   (13-AL-27(4-BE-9,FUS),,SIG)
FACILITY   (VDGT,3ARGCNE) The 20UD TANDAR laboratory.
DETECTOR   (TELES,IOCH,SIBAR) A large ionization chamber,
           followed by a surface barrier detector.
SAMPLE     The aluminum target thickness was approximately
           80 ug/cm2, a thin gold layer of 10 ug/cm2 was
           evaporated on it for normalization purposes.
ANALYSIS   (INTAD) Angular distributions were obtained at four
           different angles (10, 12, 15, 20). The maxima of the
           angular distributions were located near 12 degr. and
           therefore the experimental angular distributions
           covered around 80% of the complete angular
           distribution.
CORRECTION The extrapolation to the most forward part of the
           distributions was performed with the use of the
           shape of the theoretical predictions obtained by the
           statistical code PACE.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) The overall fusion cross section error is
           of the order of 10-15%. No information about source of
           uncertainty.
ADD-RES    (COMP) With data 9Be + 29Si and 11B + 27Al
STATUS     (TABLE,,R.M.Anjos+,J,PL/B,534,45,2002) Data
                                            presented on fig.3
HISTORY    (20260203U) SD: STATUS added. REL-REF deleted (info is
           given in ADD-RES). ERR-T -> DATA-ERR.
ENDBIB              25
