SUBENT        A0554003   20260203   20260327   20260327       A130
BIB                 11         28
REACTION   (4-BE-9(9-F-19,FUS),,SIG)
FACILITY   (VDGT,3BZLUSP) 8UD Pelletron laboratory
DETECTOR   (TELES,IOCH,SI) A large anode-splitted ionization
           chamber and a position sensitive silicon detector.
SAMPLE     The 9Be target thickness was approximately 80 ug/cm2,
           deposited onto carbon backing of ~10 ug/cm2, a thin
           gold layer of 10 ug/cm2, was evaporated on it for
           normalization purposes.
REL-REF    (R,,R.M.Anjos+,J,PR/C,49,2018,1994)
            The data for 18O + 10B and 17O + 11B.
ANALYSIS   (INTAD) Angular distributions were obtained in the
           range 7 - 37 degr. The maxima of the angular
           distributions were located near 12 degr., and
           therefore the experimental angular distributions
           covered around 80% of the complete angular
           distribution.
CORRECTION The extrapolation to the most forward part of the
           distributions was performed with the use of the
           shape of the theoretical predictions obtained by the
           statistical code PACE.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) The overall fusion cross section error is
           of the order of 10-15%. No information about source of
           uncertainty.
ADD-RES    (COMP) With data 18O + 10B and 17O + 11B.
STATUS     (TABLE,,R.M.Anjos+,J,PL/B,534,45,2002) Data
                                             presented on fig.1
HISTORY    (20260203U) SD: STATUS added. REL-REF deleted (info is
           given in ADD-RES). ERR-T -> DATA-ERR.
ENDBIB              28
